  <p>Although the average support for part-time undergraduate students is around &pound;1,100 in each year, the majority of such students (72-73%) receive &pound;500 in financial support from SAAS. The average however includes the Disabled Student&rsquo;s Allowance (DSA) payable to some students.</p>

  <p>&quot;Support&quot; refers to tuition fees (or tuition fee loans for those studying elsewhere in the UK) and/or awards and/or maintenance loans.</p>

  <p>These tables do not include students on the Nursing and Midwifery Bursary Scheme. Academic year 2006-07 is latest for which data from SAAS is available.</p>

